wikipedia_page.main: Augustine Patrick Kelly MC (1 January 1894 in Dublin, Ireland – 12 May 1960 in Hackney, London, England) was an Irish cricketer. A right-handed batsman and wicket-keeper, he played 25 times for the Ireland cricket team between 1920 and 1930 including thirteen first-class matches. He also played first-class cricket for Dublin University.
